    "According to Bock (2022) and Wu et al. (2019), in order to predict production and claim its control, crop disease severity is regarded as a crucial metric for assessing the disease's level of infection.",
    "Bock (2022) elaborates further that plant disease severity is the quantification, mainly the intensity of disease symptoms on individual units, and thus is the basis for a plethora of research and applied purposes in plant pathology and related disciplines.",
    "302 Page 4 of 35",
